description: A Roman-era bridge or causeway, possibly known as "Pons Zitha". Various subsequent versions are attested, and there may have been antecedents. All are thought to have been roughly coincident with the modern causeway, although archaeological evidence is meager to non-existent.
details: The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: between Meninge and Ad Pontem
